headshotImage.longCaption: Junaid Siddique player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: tries to hook it away but mistimes it. However a single is enough and Ireland have won.

commentPostTextItems.html: So Ireland win comfortably by 7 wickets in the end. The man of the match is of course William Porterfield whose wonderful innings anchored Ireland's innings.
The two sides meet again tomorrow so do join us again for that. Until then it's goodbye.

milestones.description: Porterfield and Paul Stirling's 118-run partnership is IRE's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 102 between Gary Wilson and Porterfield
Mortaza has broken the record for most catches (34) in ODIs for BAN, going past Ashraful's 33

stories.title: Ireland target rankings jump
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh, 1st ODI, Belfast
stories.seoTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh: William Porterfield target rankings jump
stories.summary: William Porterfield, the Ireland captain, has said the extra motivation of moving above Zimbabwe in the ICC rankings will egg his side on to complete a 2-0 sweep

image.caption: William Porterfield's century led Ireland to an easy victory
image.longCaption: William Porterfield's century led Ireland to an easy victory, Ireland v Bangladesh, 1st ODI, Belfast, July 15, 2010

stories.title: Porterfield stars in easy Ireland win
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh, 1st ODI, Belfast
stories.seoTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh: William Porterfield stars in easy Ireland win
stories.summary: Ireland's returnees from the county circuit, William Porterfield and Boyd Rankin, combined to inflict a big defeat on Bangladesh in the first ODI in Belfast
